      public long getPropagationTime(int origin, int destination, float size)
      Returns the propagation time of a message of size Size from Origin to Destination
      Parameters:
      origin - The ID of the origin node.
      destination - The ID of the destination node.
      size - The size of the message in bytes
      Returns:
      The propagation time *in milliseconds* or -1 if the nodes are not connected.

    • getPropagationTime

      public long getPropagationTime(float throughput, float size)
      Returns the propagation time of a message of size `size` in a channel of throughput `throughput`
      Parameters:
      throughput - in Bits per Second (bps)
      size - The size of the message in bytes
      Returns:
      The propagation time *in milliseconds* or -1 if the nodes are not connected.

    • getAvgTroughput

      public float getAvgTroughput(int origin)
      Calculates the average throughput a given origin node has with the rest of the network. Based on averaging the throughput of the origin with all other nodes.
      Parameters:
      origin - The origin node for which to calculate the average throughput.
      Returns:
      The average throughput for the origin node.

    • printNetwork

      public void printNetwork()
      Prints the network matrix. Each element of the matrix represents the throughput between two nodes.
